00:00:10,020 --> 00:00:12,660
How'd you fare down at
Fort Benning, Mr. Bellowes ?

5
00:00:12,760 --> 00:00:14,130
Held my own, sir.

6
00:00:14,160 --> 00:00:16,550
Managed two degrees
inside of five years.

7
00:00:16,600 --> 00:00:19,130
Studied straight through the
summers, thanks to the GI Bill.

8
00:00:19,200 --> 00:00:21,460
All while working part-time over

9
00:00:21,461 --> 00:00:23,561
at Dexter Broadman Advertising,
I see.

10
00:00:23,620 --> 00:00:26,440
I joined their creative
side full-time after Wharton.

11
00:00:27,190 --> 00:00:28,760
I'm surprised you want

12
00:00:29,161 --> 00:00:31,661
to write ads for
our little family operation.

13
00:00:31,750 --> 00:00:34,190
Well, I'm not one for
three-martini lunches, sir.

14
00:00:34,260 --> 00:00:37,590
I have bigger ideas,
and I know how to seel them.

15
00:00:37,670 --> 00:00:38,690
Such as ?

16
00:00:38,790 --> 00:00:41,750
Well, Mr. Kemp, there's a housing
shortage here in Philly.

17
00:00:41,830 --> 00:00:45,030
I came out of the service with
Uncle Sam backing my first mortgage

18
00:00:45,100 --> 00:00:47,150
and not a patch of ground in this city
to plant my flag,

19
00:00:47,151 --> 00:00:48,751
and I am not alone.

20
00:00:48,860 --> 00:00:50,350
I don't want to build high-rises.

21
00:00:50,360 --> 00:00:52,380
I'm talking about houses, sir.

22
00:00:52,510 --> 00:00:54,710
Neighborhoods of good men
and their families.

23
00:00:54,820 --> 00:00:56,850
I want to make you the
Henry Ford of housing.

24
00:00:56,970 --> 00:00:59,040
How exactly do you plan
to do that ?

25
00:00:59,040 --> 00:01:01,350
Well, I'd like to show you.

26
00:01:01,410 --> 00:01:04,050
You're gonna have to
take a ride with me.

27
00:01:10,010 --> 00:01:14,600
Last summer, blight wrecked the corn and
potato crops as far as the eye can see.

28
00:01:14,750 --> 00:01:18,590
There's 5,500 acres
sitting in the bargain bin.

29
00:01:18,680 --> 00:01:19,850
Get to the point, son.

30
00:01:19,970 --> 00:01:23,060
Cities are crowded, dirty...
built on grids.

31
00:01:23,120 --> 00:01:25,880
Out here, the streets'll be
peaceful, winding,

32
00:01:25,881 --> 00:01:28,781
named after colleges,
flowers, pretty girls.

33
00:01:28,910 --> 00:01:32,530
Picture them lined
with ranch-style houses.

34
00:01:32,810 --> 00:01:36,820
Out front, a bright-green
yard and an apple tree.

35
00:01:36,910 --> 00:01:38,720
We'll run a print campaign.

36
00:01:38,870 --> 00:01:41,910
We'll-we'll open a...
a showroom with plenty of fanfare,

37
00:01:41,960 --> 00:01:43,350
and we'll call it...

38
00:01:43,651 --> 00:01:45,551
Libertyville.

39
00:01:45,690 --> 00:01:49,130
And when the good people of
Libertyville want groceries,

40
00:01:49,190 --> 00:01:50,960
a haircut or, God forbid, a school...

41
00:01:50,961 --> 00:01:52,761
We build those, too !

42
00:01:52,910 --> 00:01:55,440
Shopping plazas with
plenty of parking.

43
00:01:55,510 --> 00:01:57,900
Recreation centers where
kids can play baseball.

44
00:01:58,000 --> 00:01:59,650
It'll be a whole new
way of life :

45
00:01:59,951 --> 00:02:01,251
the suburbs.

46
00:02:01,310 --> 00:02:04,590
Any thoughts on financing
this boondoggle ?

47
00:02:04,700 --> 00:02:06,860
They'll buy on spec.

48
00:02:07,570 --> 00:02:11,550
Home ownership... is the cornerstone
of the American dream.

49
00:02:11,720 --> 00:02:14,330
It is what makes a man a man.

50
00:02:14,680 --> 00:02:16,950
You trust me, sir.

51
00:02:17,080 --> 00:02:20,440
We will sell out before
we break ground.

52
00:02:57,490 --> 00:03:00,530
Lilly, this is Mrs. Chisholm.

53
00:03:00,680 --> 00:03:04,500
She's got information on a murder
victim found out in Somerton in '58.

54
00:03:04,550 --> 00:03:06,080
I'm Detective Rush.

55
00:03:06,160 --> 00:03:08,500
Hello. Thank you.

56
00:03:09,090 --> 00:03:11,080
His name was Julian Bellowes.

57
00:03:11,150 --> 00:03:13,500
Met him when I first
started out as a maid.

58
00:03:13,560 --> 00:03:16,560
Gracious young man.
Worked for Harrison Kemp.

59
00:03:16,640 --> 00:03:18,010
Married the boss's daughter.

60
00:03:18,130 --> 00:03:21,660
Harrison Kemp built Libertyville, big
suburban development in Somerton.

61
00:03:21,680 --> 00:03:22,590
Is that where you met him ?

62
00:03:22,690 --> 00:03:27,000
No. The Kemps were members of
the Senators Club in Center City.

63
00:03:27,130 --> 00:03:28,420
That's where I worked.

64
00:03:28,570 --> 00:03:30,000
Place is a real "Who's Who".

65
00:03:30,130 --> 00:03:34,140
The thing is, they said Julian
was killed out in the boonies,

66
00:03:34,220 --> 00:03:36,670
but I think it happened
right there at the club.

67
00:03:36,671 --> 00:03:38,071
Why is that ?

68
00:03:38,110 --> 00:03:39,900
The night before
they found Julian,

69
00:03:39,901 --> 00:03:42,801
I was on my way to clean
the Legacy Room

70
00:03:42,920 --> 00:03:44,930
after one of
Mr. Kemp's business meetings

71
00:03:45,031 --> 00:03:47,731
when I saw Julian go back inside.

72
00:03:47,790 --> 00:03:52,110
As soon as the door closes,
a fight break out.

73
00:03:52,150 --> 00:03:55,590
All kinds of yelling, glass breaking.

74
00:03:55,690 --> 00:03:57,440
- What'd you do ?
- Ran for help.

75
00:03:57,620 --> 00:03:59,150
Nobody around.

76
00:03:59,270 --> 00:04:03,750
I got back... didn't hear a peep.

77
00:04:03,920 --> 00:04:06,690
So I looked inside.

78
00:04:22,210 --> 00:04:24,850
Never saw a meeting end like that.

79
00:04:24,950 --> 00:04:26,450
You know who else was
in there ?

80
00:04:26,580 --> 00:04:28,240
Got a list.

81
00:04:28,330 --> 00:04:30,510
Been thinking about it 50 years.

82
00:04:30,510 --> 00:04:31,790
You tell your boss ?

83
00:04:31,940 --> 00:04:33,820
He said,
"Clean up and shut up"

84
00:04:33,921 --> 00:04:36,321
if I wanted to keep my job.

85
00:04:36,370 --> 00:04:39,880
Mrs. Chisholm, why did you
wait so long to come forward ?

86
00:04:40,190 --> 00:04:42,590
Just saw my doctor.

87
00:04:43,270 --> 00:04:46,250
Time to get my house in order.

88
00:04:51,930 --> 00:04:55,090
If walls could talk,
I'm thinking these wouldn't.

89
00:04:55,220 --> 00:04:58,320
The manager says the room has
barely changed in the last 50 years.

90
00:04:58,460 --> 00:05:00,510
Picking up on a theme here.

91
00:05:00,660 --> 00:05:02,810
Mary said Julian walked
through the door

92
00:05:02,811 --> 00:05:04,611
to find his killer waiting.

93
00:05:04,680 --> 00:05:08,150
Guy approaches.
They get into it.

94
00:05:08,590 --> 00:05:10,820
Couple of swings right here.

95
00:05:12,050 --> 00:05:14,310
Somebody... crashes into this.

96
00:05:14,400 --> 00:05:17,200
The glass Mary said
she heard breaking.

97
00:05:18,780 --> 00:05:20,100
This panel's different.

98
00:05:20,101 --> 00:05:22,001
Been replaced with safety glass.

99
00:05:22,070 --> 00:05:24,140
Old leaded stuff breaks in shards,

100
00:05:24,241 --> 00:05:26,041
would have crashed down.

101
00:05:26,240 --> 00:05:30,770
Evidence from 50 years ago...
is hard to come by.

102
00:05:34,870 --> 00:05:38,160
Unless it has a place to hide.

103
00:05:45,220 --> 00:05:47,450
I got it.

104
00:05:57,990 --> 00:06:01,710
Walls may not talk, but the
floor's got something say.

105
00:06:02,260 --> 00:06:04,510
Residue... could be blood.

106
00:06:04,610 --> 00:06:05,950
Mary's right.

107
00:06:06,080 --> 00:06:10,130
Whatever ended in that field
started right here.

